==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Millepore
<hw>Mil"le*pore</hw> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧l"l⟦esl⟧*p⟦omac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>mille</ets> thousand + <ets>porus</ets> pore: cf. F.
<ets>mill⟦eacute⟧pore</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any coral of
the genus Millepora, having the surface nearly smooth, and perforated
with very minute unequal pores, or cells. The animals are hydroids, not
Anthozoa. See <er>Hydrocorallia</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Milleporite</ent>⟦br⟧
